<item>
            <title>[LIT-38] [E2] Agent Registry + versioning</title>
                <link>https://gorillalogic.atlassian.net/browse/LIT-38</link>
                <project id="11390" key="LIT">Labs Initiatives Tracker</project>
                    <description>&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Summary&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A discoverable catalog of agents with version, in/out schema, and &lt;tt&gt;agent pull&lt;/tt&gt; &#224; la Docker Hub. Breaking schema = a new release. This is what a joining team consumes on day one: instead of writing its own copy of the same agent, it pulls the canonical one. Treating agents as files in a repo turns &quot;five loggers&quot; into a row of parallel implementations nobody audits... versioning them as artifacts turns that into a catalog with eval-backed releases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Pattern&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Pattern&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Versioned storage (S3/OCI). A CLI &lt;tt&gt;agent pull &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;@&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;. Schema check on push. Contract = a YAML manifest (inputs, outputs, model recs, eval suite). Parallel versions. Observable signal = &lt;tt&gt;agents_reused / agents_authored&lt;/tt&gt; per team. The difference is between having a catalog and having a drawer full of almost-the-same.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Acceptancecriteria&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Acceptance criteria&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;An operator publishes &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;agent&amp;gt;@1.2.0&lt;/tt&gt;, another consumes it, &lt;tt&gt;1.1.0&lt;/tt&gt; keeps running in parallel; the 1.2.0 eval reports the delta vs 1.1.0.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A breaking schema change is rejected on push without a major version bump.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Reuse-vs-authored ratio is tracked per team.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Demo to Labs:&lt;/b&gt; the working PoC is presented to the Labs team (plus a Lunch &amp;amp; Learn, pending Mariana Santamar&#237;a&apos;s call).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Article:&lt;/b&gt; a piece is published laying out the architecture pattern, the PoC built, and the data collected (also pending Mariana Santamar&#237;a&apos;s call).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
